A taxi loaded with 16 passengers lost control on the N2 at Zikwazi Bridge on Wednesday, killing two passengers and injuring four others, reports the North Coast Courier. One of the deceased was a three-year-old girl. The taxi rolled and hit the concrete pillars of the bridge, crumpling the wreckage. IPSS Medical Rescue s Dylan Meyrick said the four injured were in a critical condition. The injured passengers have been taken to different hospitals. The taxi was travelling from Durban to Eshowe, said Meyrick. Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.